    "discriminators": [
     "The defining leather sound: a stick-slip creak. Physically it is friction, but the hide is stiff enough to sustain a wobbling, unstable pitch — so harmonicity sits mid-scale with HIGH inharmonicity and a wandering centroid (spectral_centroid_deviation_hz well above zero). Neither noise nor a real note.",
     "That instability is the boundary against RUBBER-FRICTION, whose squeak is brighter and holds a steadier pitch, and against PLASTIC-FRICTION, which is brighter and grittier.",
     "Cloth cannot do this at all: CLOTH-MOVEMENT has harmonicity near zero. Leather is cloth plus stiffness.",
     "Not METAL-FRICTION: a leather creak has no long ringing partials and dies the instant the motion stops."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
     "LETHRMvmt",
     "RUBRFric",
     "PLASFric",
     "LETHRHndl"
    ]
   }
